For at such a time as this it is the part of a friend either to offer consolation or to make promises. Consolation I set aside, since many people have been telling me with what courage and wisdom you were bearing the injustice of the times, and how profoundly comforted you were by the conscious- ness of what you have done, and had it in your mind to do.

Well, if this is what you are doing, you are reaping the rich reward of the excellent studies in which I know you have always been occupied, and I urge you again and again to go on doing so.
